{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01P3M9UDzb5nT9tUp8WjqCGP","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Playwright exists. I need to write e2e tests for the F26 user profile page. Since Playwright requires a running server with ClickHouse, and since ClickHouse is not running (as evidenced by the ECONNREFUSED errors during build), the e2e tests will fail when run without the server. But I should write them anyway, and note the infrastructure dependency.\n\nNow let me proceed with the HTTP checks (Phase B). I need to start the dev server in the background and check for the data-testid attributes.\n\nKey insight: Since the page is a `\"use client\"` component, it:\n1. Renders on the server initially with `loading=false, profile=null, error=null` → shows \"User not found\" with `data-testid=\"user-profile\"`\n\n\n2. After hydration on client, useEffect fires, sets `loading=true`, fetches from API, then sets profile or error\n\nFor a plain curl request to the SSR HTML, I'd get the initial server state where `data-testid=\"user-profile\"` is present but `data-testid=\"identity-cluster\"` and `data-testid=\"user-timeline\"` wouldn't be, since those require the profile to be loaded. Let me verify how Next.js actually handles SSR with \"use client\" components and their initial state.\n\nIn the App Router, client components still get server-rendered for the initial HTML, and since useState starts with `loading=false` and `profile=null`, the SSR output would show the \"User not found\" state. So those identity and timeline elements wouldn't appear in the initial HTML until the useEffect runs and fetches the data. I'm wondering if Next.js 16's breaking changes might affect this behavior, but with useState and useEffect, the initial values should always be what gets rendered server-side. Let me reconsider how to approach the HTTP checks for this test.\n\nThe real issue is that testing `data-testid=\"identity-cluster\"` and `data-testid=\"user-timeline\"` requires a running dev server with ClickHouse and seeded data, otherwise these tests will fail. The `data-testid=\"user-profile\"` appears in all branches including the loading skeleton, but the other two only show up after the profile loads. Since I can't test without ClickHouse running, I should try starting the dev server anyway to see what state the page renders in—it'll either show loading or the \"User not found\" message depending on whether the hook initializes with loading true on SSR. The real issue is that these client-side components won't be in the initial HTML from a curl request—they only appear after JavaScript runs and fetches data. So I need to decide whether to run curl checks (which will fail for the dynamic elements) or use Playwright to properly test the full client-side behavior. Looking at the sprint contract requirements, it seems the HTTP checks expect all three test IDs to be present, but that's not feasible with the current client-component architecture unless I pre-render or stream the data somehow. I need to reconsider how Next.js handles \"use client\" components during server-side rendering. Even though these components are marked for client-side interactivity, they still get SSR'd on the initial page load, so the server renders the component's initial output. Looking at the UserProfilePage component, it uses hooks like `useParams` and `useUserProfile`, and on the initial render before any data loads, the profile is null, so it would render the \"User not found\" message with the `data-testid=\"user-profile\"` attribute present in the HTML.\n\nThis means a simple HTTP request would catch that first test case, but the identity-cluster and user-timeline elements only appear after the profile data loads, which requires a browser environment and actual ClickHouse data. I should start the dev server to verify the initial HTML structure, then note that the remaining tests need Playwright for the full interaction flow.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1518,"cache_read_input_tokens":48174,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1518,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":9,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c0c6e330-1db1-48b7-b235-690b82a1cb67","uuid":"3becf895-3274-4366-99d6-aa077f860c77"}
