{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01YM3UVNCkqLmSmyReVpQVjG","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"**F26 Eval Sprint 1 — Result: NEEDS_WORK (7/10)**\n\n## Phase A results (all pass)\n\n| Check | Result |\n|-------|--------|\n| Test suite | ✅ 408 passing, 0 failing |\n| Lint | ✅ exit 0 (7 pre-existing warnings, 0 new errors) |\n| Type check | ✅ exit 0 |\n| Build | ✅ exit 0, `/users/[id]` listed as dynamic route |\n| 4 file existence checks | ✅ all present |\n\n## Phase B results (2 failures)\n\n| HTTP check | Result |\n|------------|--------|\n| `data-testid=\"user-profile\"` | ✅ present in SSR HTML |\n| `data-testid=\"identity-cluster\"` | ❌ absent from SSR HTML |\n| `data-testid=\"user-timeline\"` | ❌ absent from SSR HTML |\n\n## Root cause\n\n`src/app/users/[id]/page.tsx` is a `\"use client\"` component that fetches data in `useEffect`. The initial server render hits `loading=false, profile=null` → \"User not found\" branch. Only `data-testid=\"user-profile\"` is in the SSR HTML. The `identity-cluster` and `user-timeline` testids are gated on a loaded profile, which only happens client-side after hydration + fetch.\n\n## Required fix (for Sprint 2)\n\nRefactor `src/app/users/[id]/page.tsx` to a **Server Component**: remove `\"use client\"`, replace `useParams` + `useUserProfile` with an `async` page function that calls `getUserProfile()` from `@/lib/users` directly. This makes all three `data-testid` attributes present in the initial SSR HTML. `UserTimeline.tsx` needs no changes."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3776,"cache_read_input_tokens":55723,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":3776,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c0c6e330-1db1-48b7-b235-690b82a1cb67","uuid":